adjectives.description: indistinct (comparative more indistinct, superlative most indistinct)

entries.meaning: (of an image etc) not clearly defined or not having a sharp outline; faint or dim
examples: Synonyms: fuzzy, ill-defined; see also Thesaurus:indistinct

entries.meaning: (of a thought, idea etc) hazy or vague
examples: Synonyms: ambiguous, equivocal; see also Thesaurus:vague

entries.meaning: (of speech) difficult to understand through being muffled or slurred
